@node intro "Introduction"

AminetFileRequester is a Aminet recent mail and Aminet search tool.
It was mainly designed, because I'm a very lazy person and 
wanted a program that downloads, checks and unpacks Aminet files
automatically. But I didn't find one that fit my needs, so I wrote
AminetFileRequester.

@endnode

@node feat "Features"

The features of AminetFileRequester are:
- comfortable and easy to use MUI gui
- mailer independent through the use of rexx scripts (script for YAM is
  included, MD-II is planned)
- you can download files directly without the use of 3rd party programs
- you can request recent files via ftp-mail (supported is sending the
  request mail while you're online or exporting it to your mailer)
- auto offline function
- virus check of received files through xvs.library
- auto extraction of received files
- powerful searching functions: 
   - search for files in recent mails or on Aminet
- detects Message-of-the-Day in recent mails
- you can view readme files of uploads without getting the uploads
- very configurable
- fast and cheap
- and many many more things you have to find out yourself.... :-)

@endnode

@node req "Requierements"

You'll need:
- MUI
- a Miami compatible TCP/IP stack
- an email program (scripts for YAM included)
- a subscribtion to the "Todays recent aminet uploads" or "Weekly recent
  aminet uploads" list. If you are not already subscribed then send a mail
  to "listproc@mail.wustl.edu" and in the body "SUBSCRIBE aminet-daily
  <your emailaddress>" for the daily list or "SUBSCRIBE aminet-weekly
  <your emailaddress>" for the weekly list. You will then get every day
  or every week a list with all aminet uploads. Cool, isn't it?
- xvs.library (for virus check)
- LhA for auto extraction

@endnode

@node install "Installation"

Unpack the archive to a place of your choice on your hard drive.

@endnode

@node use "Usage"

Double click on AminetFileRequester to run it.

Explaination of the:

      @{"Menu" link menu}
      @{"Main window" link mainw}
      @{"Settings window" link settsw}
      @{"Receive window" link recvw}
      @{"Aminet search window" link aminetw}
      @{"Recent mail search window" link recentw}

@endnode

@node menu "Menu"

The @{"main window" link mainw} menu:

      @{b}Project:@{ub}

         @{u}Request by mail:@{uu}
               Request selected files by ftp mail and send request online.

         @{u}Download now:@{uu}
               Connects to your prefered Aminet site, downloads the selected files
               and saves them to disk.

         @{u}Export to mailer:@{uu}
               Requests selected uploads by ftp mail and exports the request message
               to your mailer.

         @{u}Register:@{uu}
               Click on this menu point to register AminetFileRequester. For more info
               about registering see @{"Registration" link reg}.

         @{u}About:@{uu}
               Displays some informations about AminetFileRequester.

         @{u}Quit:@{uu}
               Quits AminetFileRequester.

      @{b}Options:@{ub}

         @{u}Scan folder:@{uu}
               Scans your current mailer folder for recent mails.
               (make sure your mailer is running and the right folder is selected)

         @{u}Aminet search:@{uu}
               Opens the @{"Aminet search window" link aminetw}.

         @{u}Recent mail search:@{uu}
               Opens the @{"Recent mail search window" link recentw}.

         @{u}Display MotD:@{uu}
               Displays the Message-of-the-Day of the actual recent mail
              (only enabled if the current recent mail has a Message-of-the-Day) 

         @{u}Display readme:@{uu}
              Downloads and displays the readme file of the selected upload. 
              (only possible if you are online) 

      @{b}Settings:@{ub}

         @{u}Auto offline:@{uu} (*)
               Check this menu point to enable AminetFileRequesters auto offline
               facility. After downloading files, AminetFileRequester will go offline
               automatically. So enable this option, choose some files, click on 
               @{"Download now" link mainw}, lay back and enjoy life. AminetFileRequester
               will do the rest. :-)

         @{u}Settings:@{uu}
               Opens the settings window (see @{"Settings window" link settsw}).

         @{u}MUI Settings:@{uu}
               Opens the MUI settings window (see MUI guide).

The @{"receive window" link recvw} menu:
       
       @{b}Transfer:@{ub}
             
         @{u}Abort transfer:@{uu}
               Aborts current transfer.

         @{u}Auto offline:@{uu}
               See "Auto offline" aĖbove. This menu point was implemented to be
               able to deactivate the Auto offline function during transfer.
               Of course you can activate the Auto offline function with this
               menu point, too. :-)

@endnode

@node mainw "Main window"

GUI elements:

   @{b}Lists:@{ub}

      @{u}Mail from list:@{uu}
            All found recent mails are displayed by date in this list.
            Double click on an entry to load the recent mail into AminetFileRequester.

      @{u}Uploads list:@{uu}
            Recent mail uploads or search results are displayed in this list.
            Double click on an entry to add it to the request list.

      @{u}Request list:@{uu}
            Files you want to request/download are displayed in this list.
            Double click on an entry to remove it from the list.

   @{b}Status line:@{ub}

      @{u}Server, FTPMail, Mailsize:@{uu}
            Should be self explaining. :-)

      @{u}Auto offline:@{uu} (*)
             Check this checkmark to enable AminetFileRequesters auto offline
             facility. After downloading files, AminetFileRequester will go offline
             automatically. So enable this option, choose some files, click on 
             @{"Download now" link mainw}, lay back and enjoy life. AminetFileRequester
             will do the rest. :-)

   @{b}Buttons:@{ub}

      @{u}Scan folder:@{uu}
            Scans your current mailer folder for recent mails.
            (make sure your mailer is running and the right folder is selected)

      @{u}Aminet search:@{uu}
            Opens the @{"Aminet search window" link aminetw}.

      @{u}Recent mail search:@{uu}
            Opens the @{"Recent mail search window" link recentw}.

      @{u}Display MotD:@{uu}
            Displays the Message-of-the-Day of the actual recent mail
            (only enabled if the current recent mail has a Message-of-the-Day) 

      @{u}Display readme:@{uu}
            Downloads and displays the readme file of the selected upload. 
            (only possible if you are online) 

      @{u}Clear list:@{uu}
            Clears the uploads list.

      @{u}Download now:@{uu}
            Connects to your prefered Aminet site, downloads the selected uploads
            and saves them to disk.

      @{u}Request by ftp mail:@{uu}
            Request selected uploads by ftp mail and send the mail online.

      @{u}Export to mailer:@{uu}
            Requests selected uploads by ftp mail and exports the request mail to
            your mailer.

      @{u}Quit:@{uu}
            Quits AminetFileRequester.

@endnode

@node settsw "Settings window"

   @{b}Network page:@{ub}

      @{u}Server address:@{uu}
            Type in the address of your favourite Aminet site. (ex. "de.aminet.net" for Aminet Paderborn/Germany)

      @{u}SMTP server:@{uu}
            Type in the address of your smtp server. If you don't know the address, ask your ISP.

      @{u}Modem speed:@{uu}
            Select the speed of your connection.

      @{u}ADT results:@{uu}
            Sets the maximum number of entries returned by an Aminet search.
          

   @{b}FTPMail page:@{ub}

      @{u}Your eMail adress:@{uu}
            Type in your eMail address. 

      @{u}FTPMail address:@{uu}
            Type in the address of your prefered ftp-mail service. (ex. "ftpmail@ftp.sunet.se")

      @{u}Max. Mailsize:@{uu}
            Many ftp-mail services require to split an upload into parts, select with this
            cycle how big a part can be (maxmimal).

   @{b}Options page:@{ub}

      @{u}Auto extract archives:@{uu} (*)
            Check this checkmark to enable the auto extract feature.
            If you download uploads and have this option enabled, the upload is extracted
            to a place of your choice. (see "Extract to" below)

      @{u}Get .readme's:@{uu}
            Check this checkmark to download/request the readme files of uploads.

      @{u}Check archives:@{uu} (*)
          Check this checkmark to enable the virus check feature.
          Every downloaded upload is checked for a virus and if a virus is found,
          a message is displayed.
          NOTE: Make sure you have installed xvs.library correctly.
          WARNING: If a virus is found, only a message is displayed, AminetFileRequester
                   does not make any changes on archives or files. You have to remove
                   the virus with a virus killer!

      @{u}Delete request mail:@{uu}
            Afaik only YAM has the feature to delete a mail automatically after sending.
            Check this checkmark to delete the ftpmail request message after sending.
            (only applies if you export the request message to your mailer!)

      @{u}Close main window during transfer:@{uu}
            Check this to automatically close the main window during transfers.
            
      @{u}Scan folder at startup:@{uu} (*)
            Check this to automatically scan your actual mailer folder for recent mails
            at startup. You don't have to click on "Scan folder" anymore.

   @{b}Paths/Scripts page:@{ub}

      @{u}Save dir:@{uu}
            In this dir all downloaded files are stored.

      @{u}Extract to:@{uu}
            Received archives are extracted to this dir. (only if Auto Extract is enabled)

      @{u}Offline script:@{uu}
            Select a rexx script that makes your tcp stack hanging up the line.
            An example for Miami is included in the rexx/ dir.
            (default: rexx/MiamiOffline.rexx)
            NOTE: Always set the full path!

      @{u}Mailer script:@{uu}
            This script is used for exporting a request mail to your mailer.
            An example for YAM is included in the rexx/ dir.
            (default: rexx/ExportYAM.rexx)
            NOTE: Always set the full path!

      @{u}Folder scan script:@{uu}
            This script is used for scanning your mailer folders for recent mails.
            An example for YAM is included in the rexx/ dir.
            (default: rexx/ScanFolderYAM.rexx)
            NOTE: Always set the full path!


   @{b}Save:@{ub}
      Save settings.

   @{b}Use:@{ub}
      Use settings.

   @{b}Cancel:@{ub}
      Reload old settings and forget changes.

@endnode

@node recvw "Receive window"

    @{u}Status bar:@{uu}
          Some status info is displayed in this gauge.

    @{u}Filename:@{uu}
          Name of the file that is currently transfered.

    @{u}Directory:@{uu}
          Directory in which the file is.

    @{u}Size:@{uu}
          Filesize.

    @{u}CPS:@{uu}
          CPS means chars-per-second transfered, it indicates the speed of
          transfer. A high cps-rate indicates fast connections (e.g. 3000cps),
          a low one indicates the opposite (e.g. 989cps). 

    @{u}Remaining time:@{uu}
          Time remaining until the current file is completly transfered.

    @{u}Abort transfer:@{uu}
          Abort current transfer.

@endnode 

@node aminetw "Aminet search window"

Perform a file search on Aminet.
Type in the search string (do not use wildcards) and click on "Find file".
A window will pop up informing you about the status of the transfer.
Search results are displayed in the @{"uploads list" link mainw}.

@endnode

@node recentw

Perform a file search in recent mails. Type in the string to search for 
(use standard AmigaDos patterns) and click on "Find" to start searching.
A window will pop up informing you about the search progress.

@endnode

